   "## Concept: The agent loop\n",
   "\n",
   "The **agent loop** is the heartbeat of every harness. It repeatedly:\n",
   "\n",
   "1. Builds messages (system + history + user).\n",
   "2. Calls the model with tool schemas.\n",
   "3. If the model returns tool calls, executes them and appends results.\n",
   "4. Stops when the model returns assistant text without tools (or hits `max_turns`).\n",
   "\n",
   "**Harness Agent** centralizes this in `AIAgent`. Production agents add streaming, cancellation, compression mid-loop, and parallel tools \u2014 the control flow remains similar.\n"
  ]
 },
 {
  "cell_type": "markdown",
  "metadata": {},
  "source": [
   "## How it works\n",
   "\n",
   "```mermaid\n",
   "stateDiagram-v2\n",
   "  [*] --> BuildPrompt\n",
   "  BuildPrompt --> CallModel\n",
   "  CallModel --> HasTools: tool_calls?\n",
   "  HasTools --> Dispatch: yes\n",
   "  Dispatch --> CallModel\n",
   "  HasTools --> Done: no\n",
   "  Done --> [*]\n",
   "```\n",
   "\n",
   "Key file: `harness_agent/agent.py` \u2014 `run_conversation()` wires providers, registry, sessions, compression, and learning.\n"
  ]
 },
 {
  "cell_type": "markdown",
  "metadata": {},
  "source": [
   "## Reference implementation map\n",
   "\n",
   "| Harness Agent | Nous Research agent | OpenClaw |\n",
   "|---------------|---------------------|----------|\n",
   "| `agent.py` `AIAgent` | `run_agent.py` `AIAgent` | agent session loop |\n",
   "| `config.max_turns` | loop limits in agent config | turn policies |\n",
   "\n",
   "If `REFERENCE_REPO_PATH` is set, search upstream for `run_conversation` or `AIAgent`.\n"
  ]
 },
